</step2>
</step1>
<step1>
<ptxt>PRECAUTION OF WASHER NOZZLE ADJUSTMENT</ptxt>
<step2>
<ptxt>Do not clean or adjust the washer nozzle with a safety pin, etc. because;</ptxt>
<step3>
<ptxt>the washer nozzle tip is made of resin and could be damaged.</ptxt>
</step3>
<step3>
<ptxt>adjustment is not necessary because the washer nozzle is a spray type. If it is necessary to change the nozzle angle, replace the washer nozzle with one that has a different nozzle angle. (See page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM0000023QS000X"/>)</ptxt>
</step3>
</step2>
<step2>
<ptxt>In case the washer nozzle is clogged with wax, etc., remove it and clean the nozzle hole with a soft resin brush, etc.</ptxt>
</step2>
</step1>
